### TITLE ###
WhileBodyMutationsCarryForward
### DESCRIPTION ###
Regression for "post-loop frame discards body mutations." The body
reassigns x; post-loop y should see x's possible types from BOTH
"body never ran" (= int from base) and "body ran" (= str from
assignment). Joins to int|str.
### INPUT ###
x = 5
while true:
    x = "hello"
    break
y = x
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  x @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  x @ 3:5 -> <no-type>
  y @ 5:1 -> <no-type>
  x @ 5:5 -> str|int

# Symbol types
  x (local): str
  y (local): str|int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
WhileDivergentBodyTakesFallThrough
### DESCRIPTION ###
If the body always diverges (e.g., always returns), the post-loop
frame only reflects "body never ran." No spurious union from a body
that can't actually exit.
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: int|str):
    while type_of(x) == "int":
        return
    y = x
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  type_of @ 2:11 -> dynamic
  x @ 2:19 -> int|str
  y @ 4:5 -> <no-type>
  x @ 4:9 -> int|str

# Symbol types
  f (fn): <no-type>
  x (param): int|str
  y (local): int|str

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
WhileNarrowsBodyApplyWhenFalseOutside
### DESCRIPTION ###
Standard while + null guard: inside the body x is non-null; after
the loop x is null (whether body ran or not, condition is now
falsy).
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: int?):
    while x != null:
        a = x
    b = x
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  x @ 2:11 -> int?
  a @ 3:9 -> <no-type>
  x @ 3:13 -> int
  b @ 4:5 -> <no-type>
  x @ 4:9 -> int?

# Symbol types
  a (local): int
  b (local): int?
  f (fn): <no-type>
  x (param): int?

# Diagnostics
  (none)
